io.rouz.task

Interface TaskContext

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AsyncContext, InMemImmediateContext

    public interface TaskContext
    A context for controlling Task evaluation and TaskContext.Value computation.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  TaskContext.Value<T>
      A wrapped value with additional semantics for how the enclosed value becomes available and how computations on that value are executed.

    • Method Detail

      • evaluate

        default <T> TaskContext.Value<T> evaluate(Task<T> task)
        The entry point for evaluating a TaskContext.Value from a Task. All upstreams to the task will also be evaluated through this same method. The implementation should define how and where evaluation happens. This method is a good place to define how for instance value memoization happens.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the task result
        Parameters:
        task - The task to evaluate
        Returns:
        A value of the task result

      • value

        <T> TaskContext.Value<T> value(TaskBuilder.F0<T> value)
        Create a TaskContext.Value with semantics defined by this TaskContext
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the value
        Parameters:
        value - A value value supplier
        Returns:
        A value with added semantics

      • immediateValue

        default <T> TaskContext.Value<T> immediateValue(T value)
        Create a TaskContext.Value with semantics defined by this TaskContext
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the value
        Parameters:
        value - An actual value to wrap
        Returns:
        A value with added semantics

      • toValueList

        default <T> Collector<TaskContext.Value<T>,?,TaskContext.Value<List<T>>> toValueList()
        A Collector that collects a Stream of TaskContext.Values into a TaskContext.Value of a List. The semantics of joining TaskContext.Values is decided by this TaskContext.

      • inmem

        static TaskContext inmem()
        Create a default, in-memory, immediate TaskContext. The values produced by this context should behave like synchronously created values. All graph memoization is done completely in memory.
        Returns:
        The context

      • async

        static TaskContext async(ExecutorService executorService)
        Create an asynchronous TaskContext that executes all evaluation on the given ExecutorService.
        Parameters:
        executorService - The executor service to run evaluations on
        Returns:
        The asynchronous context
